# Ticker Folder Conventions

When creating or restructuring a ticker folder, match the market template. Always include `README.md` and `research/`. Never overwrite official PDF folders with agent analysis.

## Peer templates

| Market | Reference folder | Key paths |
|--------|------------------|-----------|
| Japan | `8697.T/` | `INDEX.csv`, numbered folders, `_scripts/download_and_organize.ps1`, `_pdf_urls.txt` |
| US | `APLD/investor-documents/` | `sec-edgar/`, `ir-{company}/`, `download_{ticker}_investor_docs.py`, `DOWNLOAD_MANIFEST.json` |
| EU / Sweden | `TEQ.ST/` | `document-index.csv`, `official-reports/`, `presentations-and-media/` |

## Required on every ticker

```
{TICKER}/
├── README.md              # company, exchange, IR links, folder map
├── research/
│   ├── thesis.md          # one-line thesis + status
│   └── reports/           # deep dives, cross-checks, refresh summaries
└── _download_log.txt      # append-only download history
```

## Agent output placement

- Official PDFs → market-specific doc folders (not `research/`)
- Marvin analysis → `{TICKER}/research/` only
- Vicki / shopbot notes → `{TICKER}/research/shopbot/`
- Third-party notes → `{TICKER}/investor-documents/research-notes/` (US) or equivalent

## Scaffold source

Copy structure from `_system/templates/ticker-scaffold/` or run `_system/scripts/scaffold_ticker.py`. Update `_system/portfolio/holdings.md` when adding a new holding.
